# Plan format — Files affected first

When creating or updating an implementation plan (CreatePlan, plan documents, or multi-step task breakdowns), **always** put a **Files affected** section immediately after the plan title — before Scope, Overview, or any other section.

## Required table

| Path | Action |
|------|--------|
| `path/to/file` | **Create** / **Edit** / **Delete** — brief note |

- Use markdown links to repo paths when possible.
- List every file that will be created, modified, or deleted.
- Optionally add **Read-only inputs** and **Not changed** subsections for clarity.

## Example

```markdown
# Add feature X

## Files affected

| Path | Action |
|------|--------|
| `src/foo.py` | **Create** |
| `README.md` | **Edit** — document feature X |


Do not skip this section for small plans; a one-row table is fine.
